review: The opening keynote set a fantastic tone for the entire event. Registration was a breeze and the staff were very helpful. The quality of accepted papers was consistently high.

conference_key: ICER - International Computing Education Research Workshop
review: The host city was a wonderful choice, with plenty to see and do. The poster sessions were buzzing with energy and great discussions.

conference_key: EPIA - Portuguese Conference on Artificial Intelligence
review: A very scenic and enjoyable location for a conference. The opening keynote set a fantastic tone for the entire event.

conference_key: ICDAR - IEEE International Conference on Document Analysis and Recognition
review: The quality of accepted papers was consistently high. The host city was a wonderful choice, with plenty to see and do.

conference_key: COCOA - Conference on Combinatorial Optimization and Applications
review: The conference seemed smaller than in previous years.

conference_key: IPDPS - IEEE International Parallel and Distributed Processing Symposium (was IPPS and SPDP)
review: This year's theme was very specific. The conference seemed smaller than in previous years.

conference_key: ACMMM - ACM Multimedia
review: Overall a positive experience, but. The organizing committee did a phenomenal job. The industry keynote provided a much-needed real-world perspective. The cost is becoming a significant barrier for students and academics from smaller institutions.

conference_key: ADCS - Australasian Document Computing Symposium
review: The weather at the location was a major downside.

conference_key: IEEE CICA - IEEE Symposium on Computational Intelligence in Control and Automation
review: The location was inconvenient and difficult to get to. Poor communication from the organizers before and during the event. Poor value for money, considering the additional costs. Networking felt cliquey and difficult for newcomers.

conference_key: PAM - Passive and Active Measurement Conference
review: Networking felt cliquey and difficult for newcomers. The location was inconvenient and difficult to get to.

conference_key: ICIN - Conference on Innovation in Clouds, Internet and Networks
review: It was a good conference, although. The catering was subpar and options were very limited. The social events were poorly planned and sparsely attended. I made several valuable connections for future collaborations.

conference_key: WMSCI - World Multi-Conference on Systemics, Cybernetics and Informatics
review: Exceptional networking opportunities with leading researchers. The keynote speakers were world-class and truly inspiring.

conference_key: UbiComp - ACM International Joint Conference on Pervasive and Ubiquitous Computing (PERVASIVE and UbiComp combined from 2013)
review: The quality of accepted papers was consistently high. The registration fee was unjustifiably high for the value provided.
